
@startuml
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam noteBackgroundColor lightyellow

class House {
  - String address
  - String buildingMaterial
  - Basement basement
  - List<Company> companies
  - List<JobLog> jobLogs
}

class Basement {
  - String name
  - int size
  - String type
  -- "earth" or "concrete"
  - int humidityLevel : only if type is "earth"
}

class SemiDetachedHouse {
  + boolean hasOwnGarden
  + int numberOfWindows
  - Carport carport
  - Garage garage
}

class Carport {
  - boolean isDoubleCarport
  - boolean hasFlatRoof
}

class Garage {
  - boolean hasAutomaticDoor
}

class Company {
  - String name
  - String address
}

class JobLog {
  - int hours
  - double price
}

' Association between House and Company
House --> "0..*" Company : serviced by
House --> "0..*" JobLog : has

' Inheritance relationships
SemiDetachedHouse <|-- House

' Composition relationships
House --> "1" Basement : has
House --> "1" Carport : has (if applicable)
House --> "1" Garage : has (if applicable)

' Specialization of Basement
Basement <|-- EarthBasement
Basement <|-- ConcreteBasement

' Optional associations for Carport and Garage
SemiDetachedHouse --> "1" Carport : has
SemiDetachedHouse --> "1" Garage : has

@enduml

### Notes:
- The `House` class is the base class, with `SemiDetachedHouse` as a derived class.
- The `Basement` class is abstract, with two concrete subclasses: `EarthBasement` and `ConcreteBasement`.
- `SemiDetachedHouse` can have either a `Carport` or a `Garage`, but not both. This is modeled using composition with optional associations.
- The `JobLog` and `Company` classes are associated with `House` to represent servicing and job records.

